-- Abu Dhabi's Waha Capital sells stake in AerLift Leasing
-- By Olzhas Auyezov
-- Sun Apr 06, 2014 01:00AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, April 6 (Reuters) - Abu Dhabi investment company Waha Capital <WAHA.AD> has sold its stake in AerLift Leasing to a newly established U.S.-based aircraft leasing platform for an undisclosed amount, Waha Capital said on Sunday.

AerLift Leasing was established in 2010, with Waha Capital owning a 60.7 percent stake, the Abu Dhabi firm said in a bourse statement.